        <h2 class='headline'><a href="/videos/daniel-levitin-on-multitasking-and-brain-evolution">How Multitasking Depletes Your Brain&#x27;s Resources — And How to Restore Concentration </a></h2>
        <p class="abstract">
          Multitasking is a myth, says McGill University Psychology Professor Daniel Levitin. Switching focus across tasks comes at a neurological cost, depleting chemicals we need to concentrate. 
        </p>
        
